To understand how Python did reorganize

61
00:03:37,738 --> 00:03:40,454
并了解这对其它语言的未来有什么意义
and what it means for the future of languages in general,

62
00:03:40,774 --> 00:03:44,438
我们必须要回到 Python 故事的源头
we have to go back to the origin of the Python tale.

63
00:03:46,550 --> 00:03:50,713
我所有代码都用 C 写 这让工作变得有些枯燥
Well, I'm writing all this code in C and it's getting kind of tedious.

64
00:03:50,841 --> 00:03:55,721
本尊驾到：吉多·范罗苏姆 Python 的仁慈的独裁者
That's the man himself, Guido van Rossum, Python's Benevolent Dictator.

65
00:03:56,105 --> 00:03:58,100
范罗苏姆曾经为
Van Rossum had worked for years at

66
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:01,764
阿姆斯特丹著名的 CWI 工作数年
Amsterdam's famous Centrum Wiskunde & Informatica,
CWI = 荷兰国家数学与计算机科学研究中心 原文为荷兰语

67
00:04:02,156 --> 00:04:05,575
在那里他协助开发了 ABC 编程语言
where he helped develop the ABC programming language.
ABC 被认为是吉多发明 Python 时非常重要的灵感来源

68
00:04:05,831 --> 00:04:09,431
现在 他将描述他使用 C 工作时
Here, he's describing the moment he was working in C

69
00:04:09,431 --> 00:04:12,574
发现对一个全新编程语言产生需求的时刻
and saw a need for a brand new language.

70
00:04:13,022 --> 00:04:18,747
仍然感觉还是有着很多 bug 并且开发速度缓慢
It still felt like there were lots of bugs and it was just slow going.

71
00:04:19,425 --> 00:04:23,950
我在想 呃 如果这里支持 ABC 语言
I was thinking, hmm, if we had an ABC implementation here,

72
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:27,123
我可以在十五分钟内写出整个登录程序
I would just write a whole login program in 15 minutes,

73
00:04:27,123 --> 00:04:31,553
然后我可以接着开发账户管理之类的功能
and then I would move onto the account management program or something,

74
00:04:31,553 --> 00:04:34,149
但是用 C 进行开发 却要花掉我一整个星期
and in C, it takes me a week each.

75
00:04:34,375 --> 00:04:39,325
我开始设想 要提出一种
I somehow started thinking about coming up with a way

76
00:04:39,325 --> 00:04:45,549
可以在 Amoeba 环境中使用 ABC 语言特性的方法
to use some of ABC's features in the Amoeba environment.

77
00:04:46,957 --> 00:04:48,572
在研究编程语言的历史时我们发现
Here's something we discovered

78
00:04:48,572 --> 00:04:51,148
在研究编程语言的历史时我们发现
in studying the history of programming languages.

79
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,174
没有什么东西是全新的
There's no such thing as brand new.

80
00:04:53,650 --> 00:04:58,366
它们全都是为了拼凑出解决方案而从旧语言借鉴来的
They all borrow from old languages in order to cobble together solutions.

81
00:04:58,366 --> 00:05:01,460
语言会不断的变化、发展、开枝散叶
Languages morph, they evolve, they branch.

82
00:05:01,908 --> 00:05:05,316
当范罗苏姆被种种可能性弄得迷茫时
When van Rossum was getting frustrated with the possibilities out there,

83
00:05:05,444 --> 00:05:10,452
他设想出一个可以弥合 C 与 Shell 编程两者间隙的编程语言
he imagined a language that could bridge the gap between C and shell programming.

84
00:05:11,125 --> 00:05:12,882
一些场景下使用 C 语言往往是牛刀杀鸡
C was often overkill,

85
00:05:12,882 --> 00:05:15,650
与此同时 用 Shell 脚本又常常让人感到繁琐
but at the same time, shell scripts felt too cumbersome.

86
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:21,618
二者之间的最佳结合点 正是 Python 的栖身之处
There was a sweet spot between the two, and that was a spot that Python filled.

87
00:05:21,938 --> 00:05:25,073
当范罗苏姆 在 1991 年首次发布 Python 时
When van Rossum first released Python in 1991,

88
00:05:25,393 --> 00:05:28,609
它的影响犹如神启 尤其是对系统管理员而言
it was a revelation, for sysadmins especially.

89
00:05:29,057 --> 00:05:31,825
这是一种前无来者 功能全面的脚本语言
Here was a full-featured scripting language

90
00:05:31,825 --> 00:05:33,875
这是一种前无来者 功能全面的脚本语言
unlike anything that had come before.

91
00:05:35,155 --> 00:05:37,126
第一次使用 Python 时
The first time that I used Python,

92
00:05:37,126 --> 00:05:38,788
我立即就爱上了它
I absolutely fell in love with it.

93
00:05:38,916 --> 00:05:40,382
这是 Emily Morehouse
That's Emily Morehouse,

94
00:05:40,574 --> 00:05:44,525
目前 Python 核心开发者中的五位女性之一
one of five women currently working as a core developer on Python.

95
00:05:44,525 --> 00:05:50,173
我最初学习的是 C++ 它与 Python 有巨大的不同
I think seeing such a stark difference between a first language like C++

96
00:05:50,173 --> 00:05:52,173
在换用 Python 之后 我觉得
and then moving into something like Python,

97
00:05:52,558 --> 00:05:58,281
你能通过感受这种不同 感受到 Python 在设计上的优雅之处
you are really able to see the elegance of the language and the language design itself.

98
00:05:58,590 --> 00:06:00,825
你不必去应付
You're not necessarily having to deal with

99
00:06:00,825 --> 00:06:05,150
内存管理的毛糙的底层实现细节
any of the hairy implementation details of memory management,

100
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:11,038
它可以既快又好地构建一些项目
and it was such a great way to build things so much faster,

101
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:16,984
更不必说它还有着如此广泛的应用领域
and build things for a much wider variety of applications.

102
00:06:18,328 --> 00:06:22,056
Python 吸引力的关键之处 就在于它的可扩展性
Key to Python's attractiveness was its extensibility.

103
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:26,387
举个例子 像 ABC 这样的语言 在设计上是固化单一的
A language like ABC, for example, is monolithic in design.

104
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:31,082
无法形成一个能够真正帮助改善它的社区
There's no way for a real community to help define how the language will work.

105
00:06:31,466 --> 00:06:32,559
反观 Python
By contrast,

106
00:06:32,650 --> 00:06:32,687
在设计之初 范罗苏姆就希望 Python 是开放的、易于扩展的

107
00:06:32,687 --> 00:06:36,799
在设计之初 范罗苏姆就希望 Python 是开放的、易于扩展的
van Rossum wanted Python to be open and extensible from the beginning.

108
00:06:37,567 --> 00:06:40,266
进行软件设计时
When approaching software design,

109
00:06:40,394 --> 00:06:46,900
你往往需要用到一些现有的软件或系统
you often will have to take either existing software or other software systems,

110
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:49,140
并且要让它们能够协同工作
and get them all to work together,

111
00:06:49,652 --> 00:06:55,625
其实软件设计的核心价值之一
and one of the very true values of how you can design software

112
00:06:55,625 --> 00:06:58,009
就在于确保它的可扩展性
is making sure that it's extensible.

113
00:06:58,521 --> 00:07:00,111
听起来不怎么费脑子
It sounds like a no-brainer,

114
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:03,967
但并非每一个语言都像 Python 这样
but not every language has achieved the level of extensibility

115
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:06,167
有着与生俱来的强可扩展性
that Python had right from the start.

116
00:07:06,743 --> 00:07:10,919
事实上 一门不具备可扩展性的语言
The truth is, if a language doesn't have extensibility baked into it,

117
00:07:10,919 --> 00:07:15,671
大概率会随着自身的发展而崩溃
there's a good chance it will end up collapsing under its own weight as it grows.

118
00:07:16,503 --> 00:07:20,743
Python 有一个非常有趣的设计
Python has been designed in a very interesting way

119
00:07:20,743 --> 00:07:25,550
它允许在其核心上进行扩展
that allows it to be extensible at its core.

120
00:07:26,254 --> 00:07:31,646
实际上 你可以在运行时环境上对系统的不同片段打补丁
You can actually patch different pieces of the system at runtime,

121
00:07:31,646 --> 00:07:35,600
假如你想要改变模块导入的方式
so if you want to switch out how modules are imported,

122
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:38,550
或者你想改变你的字符串类型或整数类型
or you want to switch out your string types or your integer types,

123
00:07:38,550 --> 00:07:43,430
Python 允许你用相当容易的方式去实现这些事
Python allows you to do all these things fairly easily.

124
00:07:44,006 --> 00:07:48,420
Python 可扩展性的核心
At the heart of Python's extensibility

125
00:07:48,420 --> 00:07:51,915
是所谓的 C 扩展 或者说是 C 模块
is something called C extensions, or C modules.

126
00:07:52,525 --> 00:07:59,773
因此 Python 在设计上就为你提供了对其它语言的切入点
So Python has actually been designed to give you an entry point to other languages,

127
00:07:59,901 --> 00:08:06,463
本质上来讲 如果你可以写出 C 扩展或 C 模块
and essentially, if you can write a C extension or a C module

128
00:08:06,719 --> 00:08:10,326
可以用它去桥接其它数百种语言
that can then bridge to hundreds of other languages,

129
00:08:12,275 --> 00:08:14,110
你可以黑入 Python
you can kind of hack Python.

130
00:08:16,075 --> 00:08:20,443
这完全取决于用户根据自身需求调整语言的能力
It's all about the user's ability to adapt the language to their own needs.

131
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:23,635
所以说 Python 按照吉多·范罗苏姆的设想
So Python, as Guido van Rossum envisioned it,

132
00:08:23,955 --> 00:08:27,363
